# 🧱 **Bootstrap – Complete Guide (v5.3)**

## 🔹 **What is Bootstrap?**

> Bootstrap is a **free, open-source front-end framework** for developing responsive and mobile-first websites using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript components.

- Created by Twitter developers (Mark Otto and Jacob Thornton).
- Latest stable version: **Bootstrap 5.3** (No dependency on jQuery anymore).

---

## 🔹 **Why Use Bootstrap?**

✅ Mobile-first
✅ Prebuilt components
✅ Responsive Grid
✅ Customizable themes
✅ Fast development
✅ Browser compatible

---

## 📁 **CDN Setup (Include in HTML)**

```html
<!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
<link
  href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
  rel="stylesheet"
/>

<!-- Bootstrap JS -->
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
```

---

## 📐 **1. Bootstrap Grid System (12-Column Layout)**

Bootstrap's grid is responsive and uses Flexbox.

```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">Column 1</div>
    <div class="col-md-6">Column 2</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### ✅ Grid Classes:

| Class        | Description                   |
| ------------ | ----------------------------- |
| `.container` | Fixed-width container         |
| `.row`       | Row wrapper for columns       |
| `.col-*`     | Columns (`col-1` to `col-12`) |
| `.col-md-*`  | Medium and up (≥768px)        |
| `.col-lg-*`  | Large and up (≥992px)         |
| `.col-auto`  | Auto width                    |

---

## 🎨 **2. Bootstrap Typography**

```html
<h1 class="display-1">Heading 1</h1>
<p class="lead">This is a lead paragraph.</p>
<p class="text-muted">Muted text</p>
<p class="text-danger">Danger text</p>
<p class="text-center">Center text</p>
```

---

## 🎨 **3. Bootstrap Colors**

```html
<p class="text-primary">Primary</p>
<p class="bg-success text-white">Success Background</p>
```

---

## 🎨 **4. Bootstrap Buttons**

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-outline-danger">Outline Danger</button>
```

### ✅ Button Types:

- `btn-primary`, `btn-secondary`, `btn-success`, `btn-danger`, `btn-warning`, `btn-info`, `btn-light`, `btn-dark`, `btn-link`
- Use `btn-lg`, `btn-sm` for sizes

---

## 🧱 **5. Forms in Bootstrap**

```html
<form>
  <div class="mb-3">
    <label class="form-label">Email address</label>
    <input type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="name@example.com" />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-3">
    <label class="form-label">Example textarea</label>
    <textarea class="form-control" rows="3"></textarea>
  </div>
  <button class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
</form>
```

---

## 🧩 **6. Bootstrap Components**

### 🔘 Alerts

```html
<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert">A simple warning alert!</div>
```

---

### 🗃 Cards

```html
<div class="card" style="width: 18rem;">
  <img src="..." class="card-img-top" />
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Card Title</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Some quick text</p>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Go</a>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

### 🎛 Navbar

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">MySite</a>
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse">
      <ul class="navbar-nav">
        <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="#">Home</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>
```

---

### 🧱 Modal

```html
<button data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#myModal" class="btn btn-info">
  Launch
</button>

<div class="modal fade" id="myModal" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">Modal title</div>
      <div class="modal-body">Hello Modal</div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

### 🧱 Carousel

```html
<div id="carouselExample" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
  <div class="carousel-inner">
    <div class="carousel-item active">
      <img src="..." class="d-block w-100" />
    </div>
    <div class="carousel-item"><img src="..." class="d-block w-100" /></div>
  </div>
  <button
    class="carousel-control-prev"
    data-bs-target="#carouselExample"
    data-bs-slide="prev"
  ></button>
  <button
    class="carousel-control-next"
    data-bs-target="#carouselExample"
    data-bs-slide="next"
  ></button>
</div>
```

---

## 🔁 **7. Utilities (Classes for Spacing, Borders, Flex, etc.)**

### 📏 Spacing

```html
<div class="m-3 p-2">Margin 3, Padding 2</div>
```

### 🎯 Flexbox

```html
<div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
  <div>Left</div>
  <div>Right</div>
</div>
```

---

## 🧠 **Important Interview Questions (with Answers)**

### Q1: What is Bootstrap and why is it used?

**A:** Bootstrap is a CSS framework for building responsive, mobile-first websites faster using pre-built UI components and utilities.

---

### Q2: What is the difference between `container` and `container-fluid`?

**A:** `container` is fixed-width and adapts at breakpoints, while `container-fluid` spans the full width of the viewport.

---

### Q3: What are the breakpoints in Bootstrap 5?

**A:**

- `xs` <576px (no class)
- `sm` ≥576px
- `md` ≥768px
- `lg` ≥992px
- `xl` ≥1200px
- `xxl` ≥1400px

---

### Q4: How do you make a form responsive in Bootstrap?

**A:** Use `form-control` class for inputs and wrap in a `container` and `row`. Use grid layout to align elements properly.

---

### Q5: How is Bootstrap 5 different from Bootstrap 4?

**A:** No jQuery dependency, improved grid, RTL support, enhanced utilities, new components like Accordion, Offcanvas, and better customization with CSS variables.

